-- 
AICO Africa of Zimbabwe Returns to Profit in Full-Year as Revenue Climbs

-- B y   B r i a n   L a t h a m
-- 
2011-06-30T08:03:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-30/aico-africa-of-zimbabwe-returns-to-profit-in-full-year-as-revenue-climbs.html
AICO Africa Ltd. (AICO) , a Zimbabwean
cotton and seed producer, posted a full-year profit of $8.95
million after a $4.3 million loss a year earlier as production
of the crops climbed.  Revenue for the year through March increased 15 percent to
$210.6 million, the Harare-based company said in a statement
published in the Herald newspaper today.  Cotton output jumped to 268,000 metric tons compared with
210,000 tons, and seed production rose 45 percent, AICO said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brian Latham in Durban, South Africa at 
 blatham@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
